JOHANNESBURG - Over the past two weeks, major South African banks have released solid financial results. According to PwC’s Banking Analysis Report, the top four banks reported R76.1-billion in combined headline earnings. READ: Capitec, Reserve Bank reassure customers their money is safe This is an increase of 5.2 percent on an annualised basis and 11.6 percent from the first half of 2017. The analysis shows pre-provision earnings improved moderately, and also reflects the difficulty in revenue generation for the year. eNCA